1️⃣ Install PostgreSQL
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib -y
2️⃣ Start & Enable PostgreSQL
sudo systemctl start postgresql
sudo systemctl enable postgresql

Check status:

sudo systemctl status postgresql
3️⃣ Access PostgreSQL Shell

Switch to postgres user:

sudo -i -u postgres

Open PostgreSQL CLI:

psql
4️⃣ Create Database & User
Create database
CREATE DATABASE myappdb;
Create user
CREATE USER myuser WITH PASSWORD 'strongpassword';
Grant privileges
ALTER ROLE myuser SET client_encoding TO 'utf8';
ALTER ROLE myuser SET default_transaction_isolation TO 'read committed';
ALTER ROLE myuser SET timezone TO 'UTC';

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE myappdb TO myuser;
5️⃣ Exit PostgreSQL
\q

Exit postgres user:

exit
6️⃣ Enable Remote Connections (IMPORTANT for VPS)

Edit config:

sudo nano /etc/postgresql/*/main/postgresql.conf

Find:

#listen_addresses = 'localhost'

Change to:

listen_addresses = '*'
7️⃣ Configure Client Authentication
sudo nano /etc/postgresql/*/main/pg_hba.conf

Add this line at bottom:

host    all             all             0.0.0.0/0               md5

👉 This allows password-based connections

8️⃣ Restart PostgreSQL
sudo systemctl restart postgresql
9️⃣ Allow Port in Firewall
sudo ufw allow 5432
sudo ufw allow 'OpenSSH'
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw status
🔐 10️⃣ (IMPORTANT) Security Best Practices

Instead of allowing all IPs:

👉 Replace this:

0.0.0.0/0

👉 With your IP:

your-ip-address/32
🔗 PostgreSQL Connection URI
postgresql://myuser:strongpassword@your-vps-ip:5432/myappdb
✅ 11️⃣ Test Connection

From local system:

psql -h your-vps-ip -U myuser -d myappdb -p 5432
